Flow:
1. Collect N incident hashes off-chain
2. Build Merkle tree, compute root
3. Call anchorBatch(root, metadata) - single tx
4. Store proofs off-chain for verification

Gas savings: ~21,000 gas per anchor vs ~50,000+ per individual log

@notice Anchor a batch of incidents via Merkle root
@param root Merkle root of incident hashes
@param modelId Model version identifier
@param batchSize Number of incidents in batch

@notice Verify a leaf exists in an anchored batch
@param root Previously anchored Merkle root
@param leaf The incident hash to verify
@param proof Merkle proof (array of sibling hashes)

@title NodescryptAudit
@dev On-chain audit trail for Nodescrypt security decisions
Compatible with Shardeum, Ethereum, and INCO networks

@dev Log a security incident
@param incidentId SHA256 hash of incident payload
@param action Mitigation action taken (0=PASS, 1=DELAY, 2=DROP, 3=ESCALATE)
@param modelId Identifier of ML model used

@title PolicyRegistry
@notice Registry for NodesCrypt security policies
@dev Stores policy metadata on-chain, actual policies encrypted off-chain (INCO)

Key features:
- Store policy hashes (not full policies)
- Track policy status (active/paused/deprecated)
- Per-validator policy assignments
- Event-first design for indexing

@notice Create a new policy
@param policyId Unique policy identifier
@param contentHash Hash of encrypted policy content (stored in INCO)
@param encryptionKeyId INCO encryption key identifier
@param version Human-readable version string

@notice Log a security incident
@param incidentId Deterministic hash of incident payload
@param action RL action taken (0-3)
@param modelId Hash of model identifier
@param riskScore Calculated risk (0-100)

